{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"156c4285-ab30-4d7b-a0ac-d86c3cbd1148","content":"The template has the core required fields but has a few issues to address before publishing:\n\n**🔴 Functional bug:**\n- The `Framework` symbol is missing a `replaces` property (e.g., `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"`). Without it, the chosen framework value never gets substituted into project files — the parameter does nothing.\n\n**🟡 Recommended for NuGet packs:**\n- **Missing `$schema`** — add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation/editor support.\n- **Missing `groupIdentity`** — needed so multiple versions of this template can coexist in a NuGet pack (e.g., `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"`).\n- **Missing `precedence`** — works with `groupIdentity` for version resolution.\n- **No `postActions`** — consider adding a `dotnet restore` post-action so the generated project is immediately buildable.\n\n**✅ Looks good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `sourceName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags` are all present and valid.\n\n**Verdict:** Not ready yet — at minimum fix the `Framework` symbol so it actually works.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2e60ff57-8959-45e2-b969-0533b4cb0f8e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nIssues I can spot:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but recommended for validation and editor support.\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet template packs so multiple versions of the same template can coexist.\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Related to groupIdentity, helps with version resolution.\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Minor, but good practice for project templates.\n5. **The `Framework` symbol** — The parameter name `Framework` is conventionally used, but it should have a `replaces` property to actually substitute the value in the project file (e.g., replacing the `<TargetFramework>` value). Without `replaces`, selecting a framework won't actually change anything in the generated project.\n\n\n6. **Missing `defaultName`** — Not critical but nice to have.\n7. **No `postActions`** — Optional, but commonly includes restore NuGet packages.\n\nFor publishing, the core metadata is all there, but the `Framework` symbol won't function without a `replaces` property, and adding `$schema` and `groupIdentity` would strengthen the template pack for NuGet distribution.","outputTokens":675,"requestId":"33DB:1C1C65:1E82C20:22603C8:69E81BC3"},"id":"6bc57eb7-d797-42d5-bf54-4636412b8202","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:52:35.226Z","parentId":"f79f1bdc-8efe-476f-acec-5bd82c9a2831"}
